Found it. **Line 2041–2043** is the bug:

```ts
// Ranged monsters try to keep distance — if they're within range, don't move closer
if (monRange > 1 && dist <= monRange) {
  return;  // ← stops ALL ranged monsters from moving when player is within their range
}
```

This fires when a ranged monster is within range but has **no LOS** (blocked by a wall). The ranged attack check above (line 2019) already handles the "in range + has LOS" case with a `return`. So this second check catches "in range, no LOS" — and just does nothing. The monster never moves to get LOS, so it's permanently frozen until the player comes to it.

With 25 monsters now having `attackRange >= 3`, nearly every monster in the dungeon hits this condition and stops moving entirely. The fix: ranged monsters without LOS should still try to move toward the player to find a clear shot.
